      <title>Happy Easter!</title>
      <link>http://www.propertyflaunt.com/blog/index.php?blog=1&amp;title=happy_easter&amp;more=1&amp;c=1&amp;tb=1&amp;pb=1</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 21 Mar 2008 13:47:45 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
      <category domain="main">Selling</category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">38@http://www.propertyflaunt.com/blog/</guid>
      <description>Hey,

We hope your well and looking forward to enjoying the Easter break.British summer time officially begins but unfortumately the U.K market is still over-cast.The message and questions in the press are beginning to become some what repetetive, which only highlights the level of uncertainty in the future of our property market.

It seems that no-one is safe, Buy-to-let landlords, interest only home-owners and even first time buyers in what you would assume would be the perfect condition to get their foot in the door are falling victim to the tight criteria of the risk adverse mortgage companies and excessively expensive arrangement fee's!

One great indicator to look for in predicting the market is to keep a close eye on the activities of the National House builders and developers in and around the country, (increased incentives to buy are a clear give away).Upon doing so it is clear to see that even the bigger players are struggling and taking an extra careful look at their bottom line.Persimmon Homes have made massive cuts in staff and are reluctant to increase their land bank and recently Taylor Wimpey reported massive lossess as a result of their American activities.Right across the board the share prices of house builders and developers have plumeted.

In a week where both Gold and Oil have fallen in value by 10% there was always going to be casualties and the U.K market is no exception.What is already clear is that sellers have no choice but to be realistic with their prices. Miles Shipside, commercial director of Rightmove, reckons that there is a large gap between sellers' expectation and buyers' ability to pay.The buyers lack of ability is down to many factors but as we mentioned before there is a distinct lack of lenders,around half the lenders to choose from compared to last year.

In a slow market we know how hard it is to find a buyer, if you want to increase the exposure of your property to over an extra 3.5 million buyers for a low cost one off fee register now at: http://www.propertyflaunt.com/register.php?si=1 it could'nt be easier!

Enjoy your Easter break!

Untill next time, Good luck in all your property persuits.

The Property Flaunt Team
www.propertyflaunt.com&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/property-flaunt/Property_Flaunt-Happy_Easter.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hey,</p>

<p>We hope your well and looking forward to enjoying the Easter break.British summer time officially begins but unfortumately the U.K market is still over-cast.The message and questions in the press are beginning to become some what repetetive, which only highlights the level of uncertainty in the future of our property market.</p>

<p>It seems that no-one is safe, Buy-to-let landlords, interest only home-owners and even first time buyers in what you would assume would be the perfect condition to get their foot in the door are falling victim to the tight criteria of the risk adverse mortgage companies and excessively expensive arrangement fee&#8217;s!</p>

<p>One great indicator to look for in predicting the market is to keep a close eye on the activities of the National House builders and developers in and around the country, (increased incentives to buy are a clear give away).Upon doing so it is clear to see that even the bigger players are struggling and taking an extra careful look at their bottom line.Persimmon Homes have made massive cuts in staff and are reluctant to increase their land bank and recently Taylor Wimpey reported massive lossess as a result of their American activities.Right across the board the share prices of house builders and developers have plumeted.</p>

<p>In a week where both Gold and Oil have fallen in value by 10% there was always going to be casualties and the U.K market is no exception.What is already clear is that sellers have no choice but to be realistic with their prices. Miles Shipside, commercial director of Rightmove, reckons that there is a large gap between sellers&#8217; expectation and buyers&#8217; ability to pay.The buyers lack of ability is down to many factors but as we mentioned before there is a distinct lack of lenders,around half the lenders to choose from compared to last year.</p>

<p>In a slow market we know how hard it is to find a buyer, if you want to increase the exposure of your property to over an extra 3.5 million buyers for a low cost one off fee register now at: <a href="http://www.propertyflaunt.com/register.php?si=1">http://www.propertyflaunt.com/register.php?si=1</a> it could&#8217;nt be easier!</p>

<p>Enjoy your Easter break!</p>

<p>Untill next time, Good luck in all your property persuits.</p>

