      <description>Hello There!

We expect you had a wonderfull Christmas and are continuing to enjoy the holidays.Welcome to the latest installment of the Property Flaunt news and goings on.
In the run up to the new year it seems that the U.K press seem to have a festive time in expressing their opinions in how the U.K property market is going unfold in the new year.The mortgage lenders and Economic Editors continue to agree and disagree on how the back end of the new year will end up.One thing they all seem to agree on though is that it is all negative, being dubbed the 'Great Credit Crunch' the great debate is just how bad will it get? 
Prices will indeed fall, reposessions are set to soar and properties will be harder to sell,one thing that we must remember however is that like the seasons the U.K property market is a cycle.Some Winters are longer than others but ultimately the Spring will arrive.There is an American philosopher called Jim Rohn who explains the metaphor of the seasons in such a way we believe it will help you or indeed anyone, in times when your circumstance may not be in the direction you had hoped for. 
Again during this year coming if we can be of help to you then we would be delighted too, we would love the opportunity to assist you in any problems you may have.If you would like to market your property with Property Flaunt simply click Register or visit www.PropertyFlaunt.com. By registering with Property Flaunt you can expose your Property to over an extra 3.5 million home-buyers this massively increases your chances of a sale weather with an Estate Agent or not.
As mentioned repossessions are set to increase in 2008.We have experience of the troubles that such financial struggles can impose upon some-ones life and understand the full extent of the pain caused.If you expereince any such problems please contact us, we are here for you if you require any advice or guidance you can e-mail or phone us we would be glad to be able to put your mind at ease, we have in the past helped people in a similar circumstance through our Quick Sale service regardless of how far along the repossession is we may be able to buy your proeprty and rent it back to you.
In the meantime we have made a Video Tutorial of how to market your property on Property Flaunt.It is now on You Tube. Check it out and leave a comment: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3WbGaBAsCqA
Well unitil next time, we do hope that you enjoy the new years celebrations.

Good luck in all your Property Persuits!

The Property Flaunt Team
